The paper describes a tool for generating loop invariants using program synthesis techniques. This involves inferring preconditions and using them to grow the set of features on demand. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category, as it deals with techniques for generating code. Additionally, the paper involves software engineering (cs.SE) as it aims to guarantee correctness of a program with respect to a given specification. The paper also involves logic (cs.LO) as it deals with loop invariants, which are logical statements that hold true throughout the execution of a loop. The use of program synthesis techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
